//Duckett JS book Chapter 3 (first part): “Functions, Methods, and Objects” (pp.86-99 ONLY)//
*declaring a function:
    function sayHello(){
        document.write('Hello');
    }

 calling:
    sayHello();

*declaring a function that need information:
    function getArea(width, height){
        return width * height;
    }

 calling:
    get Area(3,5) or wallWidth =3;
                     wallHeight = 5;
                     getArea(wallWidth, wallHeight);
    
* get a single value out of function:
    function calculateArea(width, height){
        var area = width * height;
        return area;
    }

 calling:
    var wallOne = calculateArea(3,5);
    var wallTwo = calculateArea(8,5);

* geting multiple values out of a function (use return array):
    function getSize(width, height, depth){
        var area = width * height;
        var volumn = width * height * depth;
        var sizes = [area,volumn];
        return sizes;
    }
 calling:
    var areaOne = getSize(3,2,3)[0];
    var volumnOne = getSize(3,2,3)[1];

* Function Expression (anonymous function):
var area = function(width, height){
    return widith * height
}
var size = area(3,4);

* IIFE (immediately invoked function expressions):
    var area (function(){
        var width =3;
        var height =2;
        return width * height;
    }() )

*Global variable and Local variable
    -Global variable use more memory.
    -local variable ae only remembered during the period of time that a function is being excuted.

*Function expression and IIFE are used for code that only need to run once within a task.



//Duckett HTML book Chapter 4: Ch.4 “Links” (pp.74-93)//

*Link Format:
     <a href = "xxxx">IMBD</a>

1. Linking to other sites: use Absoute URL
2. Linking to other pages on the same site: can use a shorthand Relative URL

*Directory structure:
-Every page and every imago on a website has a URL.
    URL: domain name + path     eg1. www.example.com/index.html     eg2. www.example.com/index.html/images/logo.gif
-Root folder: 
    index.html (homepage for the entire site)
    individul foders for the movies,muisc..
-sub-directory folder: 
    index.html (homepage for that section)
    reviews.html
    listings.html

*How to write a Relative URL
level1 folder
level2 folder
level3 folder
-Same folder: "review.html"
-link from evel1 to level 2/level 3 folder: "level2/xxxxxx/xxx/review.html" (start from level1's next level to the target file)
-link from level 2 to level 1 folder: "../index.html"
-link from level 3 to level 1 folder: "../../index.html"

*Email links (mailto)
    <a href="mailto:jon@example.com">Email Jon</a>

*Open links in a new window (target)
    <a href="http:///www.imdb.com" target ="_blank">Internet Movie Database</a>

3. Linking to a specifc part of the same page



